      "description": "Available is a concours-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit is a mechanical masterpiece, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS system to achieve a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers precise gate engagement, paired with a factory-spec M-Variable limited-slip differential for optimal torque distribution. This specimen has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including a verified rod bearing service and a proactive subframe reinforcement to ensure chassis rigidity. The suspension geometry remains true, and the factory-spec damping provides the quintessential telepathic feedback these E46 units are known for. With zero oxidation on the undercarriage and a flawless exterior finish, this is an investment-quality example for the discerning driver.",
